quoted in 100 \u00b5l volumes and stored at -20 \u00b0C.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834164,"guid":"549FE14264EE458B9FDF675EA5562A7E","previous_id":834163,"previous_guid":"CAC7C1072023472A9B69ABDE5D81D760","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"85C0B1812C924663A33642B8109170B5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Plasmid Preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6FDFCFE954D14CCD90F006240A8FD37D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The reporter plasmid stock (in this case of plasmid <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">RPS9proMco-eGFP<\/span><span>) is prepared by transforming the purchased plasmid into <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Escherichia coli<\/span><span> (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli<\/span><span>) XL-Blue Competent Cells according to the manufacturer\u2019s instructions.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834165,"guid":"B5A38FEE18314BB28A3D7B446D2AD43A","previous_id":834164,"previous_guid":"549FE14264EE458B9FDF675EA5562A7E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0ABF9491E7004F44AFABE0CEB6F0DCC9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Plasmid Preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"ED318F6E9D674A1CAD6898E1716E0C02","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Grow the transformed <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli<\/span><span> cells on LB-Ampicillin (LB-Amp) plates (final concentration 100 \u00b5g ml<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-1<\/span><span>) at 37\u00b0C overnight (16-18 hr).<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834166,"guid":"1043E747A7394A40AB70EECD9CA88BF1","previous_id":834165,"previous_guid":"B5A38FEE18314BB28A3D7B446D2AD43A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"315EB15E0B0A4150B72E88BD1E0CF88C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Plasmid Preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A559566F60DC454C9B1F266B7507D40D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Pick one colony and inoculate into 5 ml of liquid LB Amp medium (final concentration 100 \u00b5g ml<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-1<\/span><span>) at 37\u00b0C and ~250 rpm for ~16hr.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834167,"guid":"753E853A21984F4CA6F268F4E69C0A6F","previous_id":834166,"previous_guid":"1043E747A7394A40AB70EECD9CA88BF1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2DCC52050BCA4FE786211771E3694905","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Plasmid Preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"993154EB86944005B3990F3478FB5287","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Centrifuge the culture at 6000 x g for 10 min. Remove the supernatant and resuspend the remaining pellet in 5 ml of LB medium. Use 2 ml of this cell suspension to inoculate 220 ml of LB-Amp medium (final concentration final concentration 100 \u00b5g ml<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-1<\/span><span>) and grow at 37\u00b0C and ~200 rpm for ~16 hr.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834168,"guid":"9BD3FC82DA224778AA6E92B1BF517149","previous_id":834167,"previous_guid":"753E853A21984F4CA6F268F4E69C0A6F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6D01FAA9DB764AA29A72F2BA1EB54B5B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Plasmid Preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E6B4F40D9A2C4AAAA0673B04DC117651","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Purify the plasmid using the Qiagen Maxi Prep Kit according to the manufacturer\u2019s instructions.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834169,"guid":"5108F167394B41AB94C4724EA0FAB8CC","previous_id":834168,"previous_guid":"9BD3FC82DA224778AA6E92B1BF517149","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8F99FAF718BF412096197A4F1EF33B43","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1D1A4508CA8D49608DF2CD80B7527504","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Quantify the plasmid concentration on a NanoDrop\u2122 One\/OneC Microvolume UV-Vis Spectrophotometer. Aim for a plasmid concentration of 5-10 \u00b5g \u00b5l<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-1<\/span><span> (ideally 10 \u00b5g \u00b5l<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-1<\/span><span>). Aliquot the plasmid into 1.7 ml microcentrifuge tubes and store at -20\u00b0C.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834170,"guid":"C9BA782E87864EBD913C5ECFEB143627","previous_id":834171,"previous_guid":"69B2B07065E642189CF895BC20F40491","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A75F1546DF3C4BB9A92362FFF2B8287C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"86B08982B86444A9A3CB6972A979F36F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Prepare L1 medium (2) in a natural seawater base adjusted to a salinity of 22 PSU (e.g. per liter: 550 ml of natural seawater from the North Eastern Pacific, 36 PSU) + 450 ml 18.2 M\u03a9\u00b7cm MilliQ H<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>O). Other seawaters supporting the growth of this strain and details on how to prepare medium can be found at (https:\/\/www.mbari.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/11\/KASW.pdf).<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834171,"guid":"69B2B07065E642189CF895BC20F40491","previous_id":834169,"previous_guid":"5108F167394B41AB94C4724EA0FAB8CC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A9F2AF0C674F4B2CA7324E9E88E89BA7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Culturing M. commoda"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1108F95ECE6340B6A64D10AE4AC85D4F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The growth chamber should be set to a 14:10-h light:dark cycle (~140 \u00b5mol photon m<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-2<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:super;\">s<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-1<\/span><span> photosynthetically active radiation, PAR), 21\u00b0C.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834172,"guid":"20081F247A7C4FC9887896E76A23CA7C","previous_id":834170,"previous_guid":"C9BA782E87864EBD913C5ECFEB143627","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B9DA16E83F5540248CEBB5F1AFADF1A7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"62E25A7185C545D8B75855F26709C008","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Transfer the culture approximately every 3 days (we monitor daily on a flow cytometer) to a density of 4 x 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6<\/span><span> cells ml<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-1<\/span><span>. For transformation experiments maintain <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">M. commoda<\/span><span> in mid-exponential growth for \u226510 generations. The expected growth rate in these conditions is 0.56 \u00b1 0.06 day<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-1<\/span><span>.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834173,"guid":"DEAB3A32DAD544389A3D617EF2A3FB79","previous_id":834172,"previous_guid":"20081F247A7C4FC9887896E76A23CA7C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"02974764103D41A9B3ED548B1BB595D6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transformation Instrument and Nucleofection preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2C93D469AB1F4DFF9A3A5567B461233A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>For transformation use the Lonza 4D- Nucleofector<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">TM<\/span><span> System (X Unit AAF-1002X, Core Unit AAF-1002B, 96-well Shuttle AAM-1001S). Full details on instrumental setup can be found in the Lonza manual. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":834174,"guid":"F40682FA1F8647799A0D881583BB5492","previous_id":834173,"previous_guid":"DEAB3A32DAD544389A3